cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically text coherence modeling, and proposes a novel technique for learning sentence embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper involves self-supervision, which is a technique used in unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves document structuring and information retrieval, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a likely category. Finally, the paper uses visual heuristics, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category as well.
